window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>She's my best friend's little sister…and my biggest secret.</b></p> <p><b>Logan</b></p> <p>It’s been two years since I left for college; the last time I saw Isla. But when she shows up on my doorstep, the last thing I’m expecting is old feelings to resurface.</p> <p>Growing up, we were friends, until everything started to shift.</p> <p>Our friendship turned into stolen kisses and forbidden touches, but we agreed it could never be anything more.</p> <p>Not when her brother was my best friend.</p> <p>Leaving Clifton Falls meant leaving the past behind too. Hockey is my life now, more so than before, and Isla is a distraction.</p> <p>But what happens when the lines begin to blur and she becomes the only thing I can see?</p> <p><b>Isla</b></p> <p>Logan Knight: star hockey player, my brother's best friend, and the first boy I ever loved. But we could never be more than friends.</p> <p>He broke my heart when he left for college, and now, two years later, he's back in my life and my new roommate.</p> <p>Old feelings resurface and our friendship is put to the test.</p> <p>I've tried to resist him as long as I could, but Logan has a way of knocking down every wall I've built around my heart.</p> <p>It's only a matter of time before our secret comes to light and when it finally does, will Logan be the one to protect my heart?</p>"; 
